Yeah, hurry up, hurry up.

515
00:25:45,629 --> 00:25:46,964
All right.

516
00:25:48,882 --> 00:25:51,176
You got five seconds
before I get fired!

517
00:25:51,260 --> 00:25:53,262
Jimmy's on his way
to kill Nicky.

518
00:25:53,345 --> 00:25:54,471
Really?

519
00:25:54,596 --> 00:25:57,099
I thought he was doin' that
this afternoon. I'm goin'.

520
00:25:57,182 --> 00:25:59,142
Tommy, it's for real
this time.

521
00:25:59,184 --> 00:26:00,102
He's goin' down
to Nicky's bar,

522
00:26:00,269 --> 00:26:01,520
he's got a gun.

523
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:02,604
Why? What happened?

524
00:26:02,688 --> 00:26:03,730
Nicky called the bar,

525
00:26:03,856 --> 00:26:04,815
said he wanted to make
some kind of a deal.

526
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:07,109
But he only wanted
to talk to you.

527
00:26:07,359 --> 00:26:08,694
Look, Nicky made a jerk
out of him, Tommy.

528
00:26:08,777 --> 00:26:09,903
He said he was comin',

529
00:26:09,987 --> 00:26:11,864
then made him wait
at the bar for two hours.

530
00:26:12,072 --> 00:26:13,615
They laughed at him.

531
00:26:13,699 --> 00:26:16,326
JOEY. Now, Tommy had seen
what Jimmy did to people

532
00:26:16,368 --> 00:26:17,870
who tried to make a jerk
out of him.

533
00:26:17,911 --> 00:26:19,121
Give me your cell phone.

534
00:26:28,130 --> 00:26:29,548
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

535
00:26:29,756 --> 00:26:31,550
Beautiful, isn't she?

536
00:26:34,219 --> 00:26:36,054
Nicky, phone.

537
00:26:36,597 --> 00:26:38,140
A hundred dollars,
who do you think that is?

538
00:26:38,223 --> 00:26:39,725
Tommy or Jimmy?

539
00:26:39,892 --> 00:26:40,934
Jimmy.

540
00:26:41,226 --> 00:26:43,270
You're gonna
owe me a hundred.

541
00:26:48,108 --> 00:26:50,694
You look really good.

542
00:26:50,736 --> 00:26:53,363
Thanks.
Why don't you go home?

543
00:26:54,156 --> 00:26:55,824
I'll see you
back here tonight.

544
00:26:56,033 --> 00:26:57,117
Okay.

545
00:26:57,201 --> 00:26:58,368
All right.

546
00:26:59,953 --> 00:27:01,914
Bye, Vincent.

547
00:27:02,915 --> 00:27:04,041
Yeah.

548
00:27:05,292 --> 00:27:06,585
Yeah?

549
00:27:06,668 --> 00:27:07,753
Nicky Cottero?

550
00:27:08,921 --> 00:27:09,922
It's Tommy.

551
00:27:10,047 --> 00:27:11,673
Tommy Donnelly.

552
00:27:14,468 --> 00:27:15,761
If you wanna talk,
I'm gonna be at Pete's,

553
00:27:15,844 --> 00:27:16,887
under the bridge.

554
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:19,723
Twenty minutes.
Don't be late.

555
00:27:20,766 --> 00:27:22,309
Go to the bar.

556
00:27:23,227 --> 00:27:24,561
What are you waitin' for?

557
00:27:24,603 --> 00:27:25,604
Okay.

558
00:27:29,358 --> 00:27:30,567
Tommy!

559
00:27:33,779 --> 00:27:34,738
All right.

560
00:27:36,907 --> 00:27:37,866
All right.

561
00:27:38,951 --> 00:27:40,077
All right,
when I mix this,

562
00:27:40,202 --> 00:27:42,621
it's gonna
start to dry,
all right?

563
00:27:42,663 --> 00:27:44,498
It's gonna dry fast,
so you gotta keep
addin' the water

564
00:27:44,581 --> 00:27:45,707
or I can't use this paint.

565
00:27:45,791 --> 00:27:47,125
I gotta go.

566
00:27:47,501 --> 00:27:48,794
Pardon me?

567
00:27:48,836 --> 00:27:49,837
I'm sorry.

568
00:27:50,462 --> 00:27:52,548
You gotta add water to this
or it's gonna dry out.

569
00:27:52,631 --> 00:27:53,966
Come on, whatever it is,
it can wait.

570
00:27:54,007 --> 00:27:55,050
It can't.

571
00:27:55,133 --> 00:27:56,802
This came from you.
You don't wanna see it?

572
00:27:58,887 --> 00:28:02,641
If you leave now,
you're fired, you know that?

573
00:28:02,641 --> 00:28:03,809
Yeah, I know.
But you're leavin'.

574
00:28:03,892 --> 00:28:04,935
Yeah.

575
00:28:04,977 --> 00:28:06,603
Do yourself a favor, kid.

576
00:28:07,145 --> 00:28:08,105
Give it up.

577
00:28:08,438 --> 00:28:09,815
'Cause if there's
somethin' else out there

578
00:28:09,898 --> 00:28:12,025
that's more important
than this,

579
00:28:12,401 --> 00:28:14,027
it always will be.

580
00:28:24,955 --> 00:28:27,291
JOEY. Now, you might think
this is the moment,

581
00:28:28,041 --> 00:28:30,836
the moment when Tommy
walked away from his dream.

582
00:28:31,336 --> 00:28:33,338
But I'm not finished yet.

583
00:28:37,426 --> 00:28:38,969
We'll find him.

584
00:28:39,678 --> 00:28:42,389
Thanks. Thanks for coming
with me today.

585
00:28:43,098 --> 00:28:44,474
(PHONE RINGING)

586
00:28:47,352 --> 00:28:48,353
Hello?

587
00:28:48,645 --> 00:28:50,606
Yeah, this is Jenny Reilly.

588
00:28:54,026 --> 00:28:55,611
Okay.

589
00:28:56,153 --> 00:28:57,821
Okay, thank you.

590
00:28:57,863 --> 00:28:58,906
Who was that?

591
00:28:58,989 --> 00:28:59,907
That was the cop
I spoke to earlier.

592
00:29:00,032 --> 00:29:01,617
We need to get a cab.

593
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:03,952
A man my dad's age
just got hit by a car.

594
00:29:13,045 --> 00:29:14,796
Does your father have any
distinguishing marks?

595
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:16,590
Scars, tattoos,
anything like that?

596
00:29:16,715 --> 00:29:17,674
No, I don't think so.

597
00:29:17,758 --> 00:29:18,800
How old is he?

598
00:29:18,884 --> 00:29:20,886
My father is, um, 56.

599
00:29:21,803 --> 00:29:24,097
We have someone.
You should make
an identification.

600
00:29:25,390 --> 00:29:27,059
Identification,
what does that mean?

601
00:29:27,142 --> 00:29:28,477
The cops said that
you had someone

602
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,103
that was hit by a car.

603
00:29:30,187 --> 00:29:32,397
That person expired
a couple of minutes ago.

604
00:29:32,439 --> 00:29:34,858
He's been listed
as a John Doe.

605
00:29:35,317 --> 00:29:36,860
I think it would be
a good idea for you

606
00:29:36,902 --> 00:29:38,403
to make an identification.

607
00:29:40,823 --> 00:29:42,074
Oh, God.

608
00:29:52,209 --> 00:29:55,087
You need me to stay
and pull the sheet back?

609
00:29:55,754 --> 00:29:56,964
I'll do it.

610
00:29:57,256 --> 00:29:58,715
You can take your time.

611
00:30:18,777 --> 00:30:20,237
Let's get out of here.

612
00:30:24,992 --> 00:30:26,451
It's not him.

613
00:31:23,175 --> 00:31:24,801
Your name Whitey?

614
00:31:24,843 --> 00:31:25,969
Who wants to know?

615
00:31:26,845 --> 00:31:28,931
Nobody asks
"Who wants to know?"
Unless it's them.

616
00:31:29,973 --> 00:31:31,266
Come on.

617
00:31:39,650 --> 00:31:41,568
The one guy who could
have had his dream,

618
00:31:41,652 --> 00:31:44,571
and made it out
of the neighborhood, Whitey.

619
00:31:44,655 --> 00:31:47,074
He was so fast,
he could have made
the Olympics

620
00:31:47,157 --> 00:31:48,158
or somethin' like that.

621
00:31:48,242 --> 00:31:50,077
But the idiot
never went out for track.

622
00:32:10,430 --> 00:32:12,224
Where the hell have you been?

623
00:32:43,797 --> 00:32:45,757
Hey, Tommy.
Thanks for comin'.

624
00:32:45,924 --> 00:32:48,635
No problem.
How you doin'?

625
00:32:49,178 --> 00:32:50,304
Good.

626
00:32:52,931 --> 00:32:54,641
Want some wine?

627
00:32:55,475 --> 00:32:56,768
What's on your mind?

628
00:33:01,773 --> 00:33:02,983
You and I both know

629
00:33:03,066 --> 00:33:04,568
that your brothers
killed Louie Downtown.

630
00:33:05,277 --> 00:33:08,363
They stole his business,
which is my business.

631
00:33:08,614 --> 00:33:10,115
No, I don't know
anything about that.

632
00:33:10,199 --> 00:33:11,241
It doesn't matter.

633
00:33:12,159 --> 00:33:13,994
It's all history.
I wanna forget
about the whole thing,

634
00:33:14,077 --> 00:33:15,496
we start from scratch.

635
00:33:17,122 --> 00:33:18,290
We start what?

636
00:33:18,707 --> 00:33:20,042
What do you think
I'm talkin' about?

637
00:33:20,834 --> 00:33:24,505
Talkin' about business.
Dokey Farrell's a dead man.

638
00:33:25,589 --> 00:33:28,175
The only thing left to do
is bury him.

639
00:33:29,468 --> 00:33:31,011
What's that got
to do with me?

640
00:33:31,094 --> 00:33:34,473
This. I could bury you
and your brothers
with Dokey,

641
00:33:34,515 --> 00:33:36,308
or we could talk
about your future.

642
00:33:38,393 --> 00:33:39,770
Hey, guys!

643
00:33:44,191 --> 00:33:45,734
Sorry I'm late.

644
00:33:48,821 --> 00:33:49,822
So,

645
00:33:51,365 --> 00:33:53,242
what we talkin' about?

646
00:33:55,035 --> 00:33:57,037
You're gonna have
to handle this.

647
00:33:57,287 --> 00:33:59,164
What I have to say
is to you.

648
00:33:59,248 --> 00:34:01,375
Can you believe this guy,
Tommy?

649
00:34:01,500 --> 00:34:03,335
Hey, did you order
pizza yet or what?

650
00:34:03,335 --> 00:34:04,336
Jimmy, what are you doin'?

651
00:34:04,378 --> 00:34:07,256
I'm listenin'.
I'm on the edge of my seat.

652
00:34:08,215 --> 00:34:10,801
Keep talkin'.
Don't stop 'cause of me.

653
00:34:10,884 --> 00:34:12,511
What happened to this kid?

654
00:34:12,594 --> 00:34:14,179
Your mother dropped him
on his head?

655
00:34:15,514 --> 00:34:17,266
Get your hands
off me, Tommy!

656
00:34:17,349 --> 00:34:19,476
Come on,
let's talk outside.

657
00:34:19,685 --> 00:34:21,353
You have somethin' to say,
say it!

658
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:23,355
This guy wants
to make us a deal.

659
00:34:23,438 --> 00:34:25,315
And I need to hear it.

660
00:34:25,399 --> 00:34:27,693
It's not about you.
It's about all of us.

661
00:34:28,193 --> 00:34:29,403
What makes him think
you're the one

662
00:34:29,486 --> 00:34:30,946
he should be talkin' to?

663
00:34:31,738 --> 00:34:33,240
You really want me
to tell you?
Yeah.

664
00:34:34,908 --> 00:34:37,953
'Cause he thinks I'm gonna
get it done and you won't.

665
00:34:39,163 --> 00:34:40,831
That what you wanna hear,
Jimmy?

666
00:34:42,249 --> 00:34:44,376
You know what, Tommy?
Party's over.

667
00:34:44,751 --> 00:34:46,837
Please, don't do anything.
He's gonna give me the gun.

668
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,964
The hell I am!
Jimmy, there's no choice here.

669
00:34:49,047 --> 00:34:50,507
Yeah, there is.

670
00:34:50,841 --> 00:34:53,302
He shoots me,
I'm still gonna shoot him.

671
00:34:54,928 --> 00:34:56,513
Son of a bitch!

672
00:34:58,682 --> 00:35:00,058
(GRUNTING)

673
00:35:00,225 --> 00:35:01,351
Let him go.

674
00:35:01,768 --> 00:35:03,770
(CHOKING)

675
00:35:04,188 --> 00:35:06,064
Tell him to let him go.

676
00:35:09,526 --> 00:35:11,862
Tell him to let him go!

677
00:35:11,904 --> 00:35:13,030
Yeah.

678
00:35:26,126 --> 00:35:27,336
Outside.

679
00:35:30,547 --> 00:35:32,049
Your guy stays.

680
00:35:32,925 --> 00:35:34,259
All right.

681
00:35:49,233 --> 00:35:50,651
What's your offer?

682
00:36:13,423 --> 00:36:17,135
(BRAKES SQUEALING)

683
00:36:19,304 --> 00:36:21,723
(CAR REVVING)

684
00:36:23,433 --> 00:36:25,394
What are you, crazy?
I could have run you over!

685
00:36:26,311 --> 00:36:27,813
Maybe you should have.

686
00:36:28,188 --> 00:36:30,065
So he give you
a good deal?

687
00:36:33,318 --> 00:36:34,903
A very good deal.

688
00:36:38,115 --> 00:36:40,492
You get to keep
Louie Downtown's action.

689
00:36:40,993 --> 00:36:43,537
Twenty percent of everything
I got goin' on with Dokey.

690
00:36:44,163 --> 00:36:46,790
All of it.
Extortion, prostitution,

691
00:36:46,832 --> 00:36:48,125
loan sharking, everything.

692
00:36:48,208 --> 00:36:49,835
What about Dokey?

693
00:36:50,210 --> 00:36:52,171
He's gonna kill Dokey.

694
00:36:52,212 --> 00:36:53,630
He's lookin' for somebody
in the neighborhood

695
00:36:53,672 --> 00:36:54,756
he can work with.

696
00:36:55,174 --> 00:36:56,550
He thinks it's us.

697
00:36:56,633 --> 00:36:58,010
You mean you.

698
00:37:03,515 --> 00:37:06,643
It is a good deal.
You took it, I hope.

699
00:37:06,727 --> 00:37:08,228
After all this?

700
00:37:08,770 --> 00:37:11,106
After all what?
Let bygones be bygones.

701
00:37:11,356 --> 00:37:13,692
It's a great thing,
it's what we always wanted.

702
00:37:15,027 --> 00:37:17,905
Now, Tommy knew Nicky
was gonna get what he wanted.

703
00:37:18,322 --> 00:37:20,449
Dokey was gonna die.

704
00:37:20,532 --> 00:37:23,869
And if Nicky had his way,
Jimmy, Sean and Kevin

705
00:37:23,911 --> 00:37:24,995
were gonna die, too.

706
00:37:25,454 --> 00:37:27,206
It was that simple.

707
00:37:33,962 --> 00:37:35,672
Did you take the deal?

708
00:37:37,466 --> 00:37:38,425
Tommy!

709
00:37:39,009 --> 00:37:40,844
Tommy, did you
take the deal?

710
00:37:41,553 --> 00:37:43,889
I hope you weren't
stupid about this.

711
00:37:46,141 --> 00:37:47,601
So what are we gonna do?

712
00:37:47,768 --> 00:37:50,145
Kill this kid
and kill his brothers?

713
00:37:50,229 --> 00:37:51,563
What do you wanna
do that for?

714
00:37:51,605 --> 00:37:53,023
You wanna ruin everything?

715
00:37:53,065 --> 00:37:54,441
What ruin everything?

716
00:37:54,525 --> 00:37:56,026
You told him
that we're gonna kill Dokey.

717
00:37:56,068 --> 00:37:57,528
Don't you think
he's gonna go
tell him that?

718
00:37:57,569 --> 00:37:59,696
I think he likes Dokey
less than we do.

719
00:38:00,948 --> 00:38:02,699
Why don't you have
another glass of wine.

720
00:38:02,741 --> 00:38:05,869
Be a little patient.
He'll come around.

721
00:38:13,752 --> 00:38:15,379
I guess I'll be goin', then.

722
00:38:15,504 --> 00:38:17,923
Thanks for lookin'
after the place.

723
00:38:19,591 --> 00:38:21,093
It's nothin'.

724
00:38:22,427 --> 00:38:23,554
Joey.

725
00:38:23,679 --> 00:38:24,680
Yeah?

726
00:38:24,805 --> 00:38:25,806
Keys.

727
00:38:26,849 --> 00:38:27,891
Oh.

728
00:38:27,933 --> 00:38:29,685
JOEY. Actually,
now that I think about it,

729
00:38:29,852 --> 00:38:31,395
no wonder I'm depressed.

730
00:38:31,854 --> 00:38:33,939
That was the day
I lost my dream, too.

731
00:38:34,314 --> 00:38:35,274
Oh?

732
00:38:35,357 --> 00:38:37,067
I always wanted to be
a short-order cook.

733
00:38:37,943 --> 00:38:39,778
So why didn't you ask her
for a job?

734
00:38:41,822 --> 00:38:43,782
I never thought of that.

735
00:39:05,721 --> 00:39:08,265
Go home, Kevin.
It's been a long day.

736
00:39:14,855 --> 00:39:16,106
I'll stay.

737
00:39:48,096 --> 00:39:49,806
It's beautiful,
ain't it?

738
00:39:50,265 --> 00:39:51,892
It's pretty cool.

739
00:39:54,269 --> 00:39:55,854
Seanie, I been takin' care
of ya, haven't I?

740
00:39:55,979 --> 00:39:57,064
Yeah.

741
00:39:58,899 --> 00:40:01,568
I believed in you,
a little bit.

742
00:40:02,277 --> 00:40:03,779
Jimmy, I'm sorry
I called Tommy.

743
00:40:03,862 --> 00:40:05,489
Nothin' to be sorry about.

744
00:40:06,907 --> 00:40:08,951
You think what you think.

745
00:40:10,077 --> 00:40:12,037
And it ain't much of me.

746
00:40:44,403 --> 00:40:45,779
I fired you.

747
00:40:47,573 --> 00:40:48,657
I know.

748
00:40:54,621 --> 00:40:56,623
I just wanted to see it.

749
00:40:58,041 --> 00:40:59,209
How it would look.

750
00:42:01,980 --> 00:42:03,815
JOEY. And that was the moment

751
00:42:03,857 --> 00:42:05,776
Tommy walked away
from his dream.

752
00:42:53,073 --> 00:42:54,908
Hey, I'm feelin'
much better now!

753
00:42:55,868 --> 00:42:58,078
(DOOR SLAMS)
You got any more
of that food left?

